---
const withBase = (path: string) => {
  const base = '/arcup';
  if (path === '/') return `${base}/`;
  return `${base}${path}`;
};

const formURL = "https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeaIq1c0a9zu0R5Z0_GHP73HxKKjDr2vcjgjoiV2L3PxSv-ww/viewform?usp=dialog";
---

<main id="main-content" class="page-shell page-how" aria-labelledby="how-title">
  
  <!-- HERO SECTION -->
  <header class="how-hero" aria-labelledby="how-title">
    <p class="hero-eyebrow">Our Framework</p>
    <h1 id="how-title">How Arc^ Works</h1>
    <p class="hero-lede">
      Most research happens behind closed doors. Results appear fully formed, polished, ready to monetize. 
      <strong>We do the opposite:</strong> document from day zero, share everything, invite scrutiny. Here's how.
    </p>
  </header>

  <!-- EARTH AS LIVING SYSTEM -->
  <section class="worldview-section surface-panel">
    <h2>Earth as Living System</h2>
    <p>
      We recognize Earth as a dynamic, emergent network of interacting systems—not a resource to extract from, 
      but a living whole we're part of. <strong>Human technology must align with Earth's regenerative capacity, 
      not work against it.</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="worldview-note">
      This understanding shapes every experiment, every design choice, every collaboration.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT WE STAND FOR -->
  <section class="commitments-section">
    <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="divider-label">what we stand for</span>
    </div>

    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>8 Core Commitments</h2>
      <p class="lead">These principles guide every decision we make at Arc^:</p>
    </header>

    <div class="commitments-grid">
      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">👥</div>
        <h3>Circle of Care</h3>
        <p>Human dignity, anti-discrimination, universal access. Everyone deserves to participate in and benefit from scientific progress.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🐾</div>
        <h3>Multi-Species Ethics</h3>
        <p>No invasive harm to non-humans. We use observation, eDNA, and non-invasive methods to study ecosystems. Design to avoid disruption.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🌱</div>
        <h3>Planetary Restoration</h3>
        <p>Technology must heal ecosystems, not just serve humans. Repair and regeneration are the measures of success.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🔄</div>
        <h3>Iterative Humility</h3>
        <p>Learning matters more than perfection. Mistakes are expected and documented. A single study isn't proof—replication builds confidence.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🌍</div>
        <h3>Global Majority Orientation</h3>
        <p>Plural perspectives, no single hegemony. We center voices from communities most impacted by environmental harm and least served by existing systems.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🔓</div>
        <h3>Openness with Responsibility</h3>
        <p>Transparent by default, with safety guardrails. Research is public from day one, but we stop if harm is likely.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🪶</div>
        <h3>Transparency & Credit</h3>
        <p>Everyone who contributes is seen. Attribution ledgers map contributions. Public outputs cite all collaborators and partners.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="commitment-card surface-panel">
        <div class="commitment-icon">🛡️</div>
        <h3>Safety & Harm Prevention</h3>
        <p>If a path trends toward weaponization, surveillance, or ecocide—we stop. Safety is non-negotiable, especially with high-voltage plasma.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- RE:TECH DESIGN APPROACH -->
  <section class="retech-section">
    <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="divider-label">our design approach</span>
    </div>

    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>RE:TECH: How We Build</h2>
      <p class="lead">RE:TECH is our design approach—how we translate values into practice. Technology stays at the edge of our fingertips, supporting rather than dominating.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="retech-flow">
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span class="flow-number">01</span>
        <h3>Re-think</h3>
        <p>Question assumptions. Ask "what world does this create?" before building anything.</p>
      </div>
      <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span class="flow-number">02</span>
        <h3>Re-align</h3>
        <p>Design with regeneration in mind. Align technology with Earth's living systems.</p>
      </div>
      <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span class="flow-number">03</span>
        <h3>Re-make</h3>
        <p>Build openly. Document from day zero. Share methods, data, and designs.</p>
      </div>
      <span class="flow-arrow">→</span>
      <div class="flow-step">
        <span class="flow-number">04</span>
        <h3>Re-share</h3>
        <p>Knowledge stays in the commons. Enable replication, adaptation, and collective improvement.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="retech-principles">
      <h3>This Means:</h3>
      <ul class="principles-checklist">
        <li>✓ Open by default, non-extractive by design</li>
        <li>✓ Future-conscious (10-year thinking)</li>
        <li>✓ Ecological interdependence (humans aren't separate from nature)</li>
        <li>✓ Safety as non-negotiable (stop if harm is likely)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

<!-- HOW WE WORK TOGETHER -->
<section class="method-section">
  <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
    <span class="divider-label">our process</span>
  </div>

  <header class="section-header">
    <h2>How We Work Together</h2>
    <p class="lead">Seven steps guide every Arc^ project:</p>
  </header>

  <article class="method-compact surface-panel">
    <h3>Example: Community Garden Testing PAW</h3>
    <p class="scenario-text">A community garden wants to test if plasma-activated water improves native plant germination. Here's the process:</p>
    
    <div class="method-flow">
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">01</span>
        <p><strong>Document Early</strong> — Hypothesis and protocols published before starting</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">02</span>
        <p><strong>Show the Work</strong> — Device specs, parameters, and data logged openly</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">03</span>
        <p><strong>Invite Review</strong> — Local experts review protocol before experiments begin</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">04</span>
        <p><strong>Track Status</strong> — Live updates with WIP markers and changelogs</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">05</span>
        <p><strong>Credit Everyone</strong> — All contributors listed in outputs</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">06</span>
        <p><strong>Co-Design</strong> — Community chooses species based on restoration goals</p>
      </div>
      
      <div class="method-item">
        <span class="method-num">07</span>
        <p><strong>Replicate</strong> — Protocol shared for testing elsewhere before broader claims</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="outcome-text"><strong>Outcome:</strong> Data stays open, hardware stays open, garden owns the knowledge.</p>
  </article>
</section>

  <!-- SAFETY SECTION -->
  <section class="safety-section">
    <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="divider-label">safety first</span>
    </div>

    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>Safety is Non-Negotiable</h2>
      <p class="lead">Plasma research involves high voltage, reactive chemistry, and ecological impacts. These requirements apply to all Arc^ work:</p>
    </header>

    <div class="safety-grid">
      <article class="safety-card surface-panel">
        <h3>⚡ Electrical Safety</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Proper grounding and isolation</li>
          <li>Personal protective equipment (PPE)</li>
          <li>High-voltage training required</li>
          <li>Equipment inspection protocols</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="safety-card surface-panel">
        <h3>🧪 Chemical Safety</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Adequate ventilation systems</li>
          <li>Reactive species monitoring</li>
          <li>Proper disposal procedures</li>
          <li>Material safety data sheets (MSDS)</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="safety-card surface-panel">
        <h3>🌿 Ecological Ethics</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Long-term monitoring plans</li>
          <li>Non-invasive research methods</li>
          <li>Baseline environmental assessments</li>
          <li>Community consent protocols</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="safety-card surface-panel">
        <h3>📋 Incident Reporting</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Failures documented publicly</li>
          <li>Near-miss reporting system</li>
          <li>Safety review before scaling</li>
          <li>Stop rules: halt if harm emerges</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="safety-note">
      <strong>If you're unsure about a procedure, ask before proceeding.</strong> Safety concerns are never an inconvenience—they're the foundation of responsible research.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- LICENSING -->
  <section class="licensing-section surface-panel">
    <h2>Licensing & Governance</h2>
    <p class="licensing-intro">All Arc^ work uses open licenses that keep knowledge in the commons:</p>
    
    <table class="licensing-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Type</th>
          <th>License</th>
          <th>Why</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Documentation</strong></td>
          <td>CC BY-NC-SA 4.0</td>
          <td>Share and adapt with attribution; commercial use requires benefit-sharing</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Hardware</strong></td>
          <td>CERN OHL-S 2.0</td>
          <td>Strong reciprocity—modifications must be shared openly</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Software</strong></td>
          <td>AGPL-3.0</td>
          <td>Network copyleft—public use requires open source</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Data</strong></td>
          <td>ODC-BY or CC BY-SA</td>
          <td>Open with attribution; derivatives must credit sources</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <p class="licensing-note">
      <strong>No patents. Ever.</strong> Knowledge generated through Arc^ stays in the commons. Commercial applications are possible, but require benefit-sharing agreements that ensure value flows back to the research community and the ecosystems we serve.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- START COLLABORATING -->
  <section class="collaborate-section">
    <div class="section-divider" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="divider-label">start collaborating</span>
    </div>

    <header class="section-header">
      <h2>Three Pathways to Contribute</h2>
      <p class="lead">Choose the path that fits your skills and interests:</p>
    </header>

    <div class="pathways-grid">
      <article class="pathway-card surface-panel">
        <div class="pathway-icon">🔬</div>
        <h3>Research</h3>
        <p>Conduct literature reviews, design experiments, analyze data, and document findings openly.</p>
        <ul class="pathway-tasks">
          <li>Review existing plasma research</li>
          <li>Design experimental protocols</li>
          <li>Analyze datasets and results</li>
          <li>Write up findings for publication</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="pathway-card surface-panel">
        <div class="pathway-icon">🛠️</div>
        <h3>Build</h3>
        <p>Create hardware designs, write safety protocols, develop tools, and improve documentation.</p>
        <ul class="pathway-tasks">
          <li>Design plasma devices (CAD, schematics)</li>
          <li>Build and test prototypes</li>
          <li>Write safety and testing protocols</li>
          <li>Develop analysis software tools</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="pathway-card surface-panel">
        <div class="pathway-icon">🌱</div>
        <h3>Apply</h3>
        <p>Test plasma-activated water in real contexts with ethical oversight and community partnership.</p>
        <ul class="pathway-tasks">
          <li>Host field trials on your land</li>
          <li>Monitor ecological outcomes</li>
          <li>Co-design with local communities</li>
          <li>Share traditional knowledge</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FINAL CTA -->
  <section class="final-cta-section">
    <h2>See These Principles in Action</h2>
    <p>Every Arc^ project follows this framework. Explore active research and find where you fit.</p>
    <div class="cta-buttons">
      <a href={withBase("/projects")} class="button button-large">Browse Open Projects</a>
      <a href={formURL} target="_blank" class="button button-outline button-large">Contact Ali</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</main>

